cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with computational topology and the construction of complexes on point data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves subsampling and graph theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of persistent homology, which is a technique used in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
